World Bank Gives Mozambique Funding for Education, Noticias Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-07-18T06:09:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/world-bank-gives-mozambique-funding-for-education-noticias-says.html
The  World Bank  will provide $161
million to  Mozambique ’s government to fund an education program,
Noticias reported, citing a statement from the lender.  Of the total, $90 million be a donation and the remainder
will be a credit under the bank’s Education for All - Fast Track
Initiative, the Maputo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 